{"title":"Cyclist Track Days bikes #25 and #26: Giant TCR and Liv Langma","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-bikes-giant-tcr-liv-langma","date":1744196960000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-bikes-giant-tcr-liv-langma\">Cyclist Track Days bikes #25 and #26: Giant TCR and Liv Langma</a></p>\n\n<p>It’s almost time to kick off our 2025 <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">Cyclist Track Days</a> events, where you can test the latest top-end bikes from the leading brands on the market. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Two new bikes added to our <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikes-cyclist-track-days-2025\">amazing lineup</a> of the bikes that you can test ride at this years Track Days are the Giant TCR and Liv Langma.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Giant TCR is the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/inside-giants-taiwan-factory\">Taiwanese manufacturer</a>‘s <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-all-round-road-race-bikes\">all-round road race bike</a>, and it’s hard to find a bike that’s been more influential than <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bike-history-giant-tcr\">the TCR</a>. <em>Cyclist </em>deputy editor James Spender reviewed most recent edition late last year and praised its handling, stiffness, light weight, aerodynamics and spec. What more could you want?</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2021/06/06085756/langmaadvsl_side_crop_jeffclarkphotography-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"langmaadvsl_side_crop_jeffclarkphotography\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Liv Langma is Giant’s women’s-specific brand Liv’s TCR equivalent, with all the same aims and a shared aesthetic, however all the details that matter are designed for women, so the bike has a completely different geometry and component sizes more suited to women’s bodies such as narrower bars and shorter cranks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Read James’s full review <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/giant-tcr-advanced-pro-road-bike-review\">here</a>.<br />Read all about the latest Liv Langma <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/liv-langma-2024\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Giant TCR and Liv Langma will be at the following Track Days events:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>26<sup>th</sup> April 2025, Odd Down Cycle Track Bath,<br />17<sup>th</sup> May 2025, Lee Valley VeloPark London,<br />7<sup>th</sup> June 2025, The Brownlee Centre, Leeds</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information on Cyclist Track Days click <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikes-cyclist-track-days-2025\">Which bikes can you test ride at Cyclist Track Days 2025?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">Cyclist Track Days 2025 info and how to get tickets</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/inside-giants-taiwan-factory\">Inside Giant’s Taiwan factory</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n 